HEADWORD: Dittied
<hw>Dit"tied</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Ditty</er>.]</ety> <def>Set, sung, or composed as a ditty; --
usually in composition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who, with his soft pipe, and smooth-<qex>dittied</qex> song.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ditto</ent>⟦br⟧
